parameters:
\n<Count Noblesse>It seems either drugs were involved or it was a mutual
takedown, but that Rui managed to capture the phantom thief.
Splendid, what an impressive feat!
\n<Count Noblesse>I'll add a bonus to your reward. Take this.
\n<Guild Master>...Is this... a \C[14]Call Wolf Stone\C[0]?

\n<Count Noblesse>No, it's a fake. I never had such a thing to begin with.
Even I don't possess one of the world's four great diamonds.
\n<Ladro>Ugh... gah... a fake...? You tricked me...!?
\n<Count Noblesse>Hey, if that guy speaks again, kick him in the stomach.

\n<Count Noblesse>But just because it's a fake doesn't mean it's worthless. It
should be worth about 1 million G. I'll give it to you. No
need to hold back.

\n<Guild Master>Hey now, aren't you being quite generous. Did you hate that
guy that much? Hah. It's hard to tell if the rich are really
generous or just pretending.

\n<Count Noblesse>Watch your mouth, commoner. I think you should gratefully
accept kindness from those above you, don't you?
\n<Guild Master>Yes, yes~ I can't help but bow to the nobility's generosity.

\n<Guild Master>...(However, even if it's a fake, it will take time to sell
this off. I'll need to carefully select a trustworthy
appraiser and dealer.)

\n<Guild Master>(Tch. What a hassle. And is that 1 million G for real?
Sounds fishy.)

\n<Count Noblesse>Then, we shall take our leave. We must judge Cats in the
higher court and throw him into prison.
\n<Ladro>P-Please, \C[14]don't let go of me!!\C[0] I might get hurt!

\n<Ladro>I may not look it, but I'm a rough woman If you let go of
me during the escort, I'll beat you all up So, \C[14]please
don't let go!\C[0]

\n<Private Soldier>Don't get cocky! You thief! Do you even understand the
situation you're in?
\n<Count Noblesse>Farewell then. It's unlikely you'll come here again.
\n<Ladro>...

\n<Guild Master>...Well, I knew a day like this would come eventually.
Ladro.

\C[14]\n<Guild Master>Not telling Rui\C[0], huh. If they knew the true identity of
the phantom thief, Rui would feel responsible. Understood.

\n<Guild Master>But to worry about Rui at a time like this. You're a tough
woman indeed. Sigh... What to do with this gemstone now.
\n<Guild Master>If it sells for a good price, I'll give it all to the kids.
\n<Radro>Here it is! As usual, please take care of it

\C[14]\n<Guild Master>A Howling Stone\C[0], huh... It's huge. Bigger than I
imagined.

\n<Radro>Try to sell it for as much as possible, okay? It was quite a
hassle to get. In various ways.

\n<Guild Master>Yeah, but this is going to take some time. I need to
carefully select a decent appraiser and a tight-lipped
seller. Tch... It's a real pain to sell a treasure of this
caliber.

\n<Radro>Make sure you manage it properly, okay? If word gets out
that we have this, it could lead to a bloodbath. The only
ones who know about it are me, the Master, and Rui.

\n<Guild Master>Rui knows about it too, huh. Hmph... I bet you lost to Rui
and begged for your life, didn't you? Am I wrong?

\n<Radro>Well, something like that. Master, you can be really sharp
sometimes. I really hate that about you.
\n<Guild Master>It's because we go way back.

\n<Guild Master>I can't turn it into cash immediately, but I'll see what I
can do. For the time being, I'll be keeping this thing. Is
that okay with you? Ah, what a hassle.
\n<Radro>Yeah. Please do. I trust you.

\n<Guild Master>But why is Rui sleeping so soundly? Take them to the inn.
They'll catch a cold and they're in the way.
\n<Radro>Their sleeping face is cute, isn't it?
\n<Rui>Mumble mumble... zzzZ
\n<Guild Master>...Well, yeah. But hurry up and take them away.

\n<Guild Master>I'm not interested in the sleeping face of a bastard. Hurry
up and take them away.
It's smoked fish. It looks very... *drools*... delicious.
